# BitNet Integration (TinyBench)

This project can support BitNet as an additional local inference backend, not a replacement for existing GGUF support.

Reference implementation and setup details: [microsoft/BitNet README](https://github.com/microsoft/BitNet?tab=readme-ov-file).

## Integration goals

- Keep architecture backend-agnostic: GGUF and BitNet should share a common runner interface.
- Treat BitNet as an opt-in provider selected per model/job.
- Preserve existing UX patterns: JSON APIs for control + SSE for streaming status/output.
- Keep Raspberry Pi and low-power devices in mind: bounded CPU usage, simple polling, minimal UI overhead.

## File and module expectations

- Add a dedicated runner in `app/services/inference/bitnet_runner.py`.
- Keep provider contracts in `app/services/inference/base.py` (abstract methods, shared typing).
- Extend `app/services/model_registry.py` to identify both GGUF and BitNet-compatible models.
- Extend `app/services/model_downloader.py` for BitNet model acquisition/setup orchestration.
- Keep path/constants in `app/config.py`; avoid hardcoded absolute paths in service code.
- If route complexity grows, move API/SSE endpoints into `app/routers/` and include routers from `app/main.py`.

## Configuration and paths

Use environment-driven configuration with safe defaults:

- `BITNET_ROOT`: local checkout/build directory for BitNet runtime.
- `BITNET_CLI_PATH`: executable/script path used for inference calls.
- `BITNET_MODELS_DIR`: directory for BitNet model assets.
- `BITNET_LOG_DIR`: optional directory for benchmark/setup logs.
- `BITNET_THREADS`: default worker thread count.
- `BITNET_CTX_SIZE`: default context size.

Also keep existing `MODELS_DIR` behavior for GGUF models. Do not mix BitNet-specific assets into unrelated directories unless intentionally designed.

## Runner behavior requirements

- `bitnet_runner.py` should implement the same logical contract as other runners:
  - synchronous/async generation entrypoint,
  - token streaming or chunk streaming callback,
  - cancellation support via job id/state flag,
  - structured error propagation.
- Use `subprocess` safely:
  - pass args as a list (no shell string concatenation),
  - enforce timeout/kill behavior for hung processes,
  - capture stdout/stderr separately for diagnostics,
  - log command metadata without leaking secrets.
- Parse incremental output defensively; BitNet CLI output format may evolve.
- Never block the event loop with long CPU/process waits; offload to worker thread/task where needed.

## Model registry and selection

- Track metadata per model:
  - `model_id`, `provider` (`gguf` or `bitnet`), local path, size (if known), readiness.
- Expose provider-aware listing to UI/API so users can choose backend explicitly.
- Validate model/provider compatibility before starting inference; fail fast with clear message.

## Download/setup workflow

- Keep download/setup idempotent.
- Prefer explicit status transitions (`queued`, `downloading`, `preparing`, `ready`, `failed`).
- For BitNet setup, support both:
  - local model directory provided by user, and
  - Hugging Face model source configured in app settings.
- Verify required artifacts after setup (model file presence, CLI accessibility).

## API and SSE conventions

- Non-stream operations remain under `/api/...` and return structured JSON errors.
- Stream generation/status over `/sse/...` with event types:
  - `status`, `token`, `metric`, `done`, `error`.
- Include `job_id` and `model_id` in relevant payloads for correlation.
- Keep payloads small; batch token events when useful to reduce frontend reflows.

## Frontend integration constraints

- No framework additions; use existing vanilla JS pattern in `app/static/js/`.
- Provider/model dropdowns must be populated from backend metadata, not hardcoded lists.
- Use `textContent` for streamed text and throttle DOM writes during long generations.
- Surface setup/inference failures with compact, user-readable messages.

## Reliability and observability

- Use `logging` (not `print`) with provider-tagged context (`provider=bitnet`, `job_id=...`).
- Log setup duration, generation duration, and cancellation events.
- Keep power sampling independent from inference loop; only correlate by shared identifiers.

## Security and safety

- Do not execute untrusted shell input from user prompts or model ids.
- Validate all filesystem paths before use.
- Avoid writing model binaries into version control paths.
- Never commit downloaded model weights or large runtime build artifacts.

## Validation checklist (after BitNet-related changes)

- `ruff check .`
- `pytest -q` (or focused tests first, then full suite)
- `python -m compileall app`
- Manual sanity checks:
  - GGUF path still works end-to-end.
  - BitNet setup reports clear status.
  - BitNet inference streams tokens and can be cancelled.
  - UI remains usable on small/mobile viewport.
